  "prompt": "How can I poke someone on Facebook?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, Facebook has evolved significantly and many features have changed or been removed over the years. The \"poke\" feature is one of those that might not be readily accessible the way it used to be. However, if the feature is still available, here are general steps you might follow to poke someone on Facebook:\n\n1. **Log into Facebook**: Open the Facebook app on your mobile device or go to the Facebook website and log in to your account.\n\n2. **Go to the Profile**: Navigate to the profile of the person you want to poke. You can do this by searching their name in the search bar.\n\n3. **Find the Poke Button**: On some profiles, you may find a \"...\" button, or more options buttons. Clicking this might bring up additional options including \"Poke.\"\n\n4. **Poke**: If the option to poke appears, click on it. This will send a poke notification to the person.\n\nKeep in mind the feature could be removed or changed after the last update. If you can't find it on the profile page, it may mean Facebook has removed or hidden the feature.\n\nIf you're not able to poke, consider sending a message or another form of interaction available on Facebook.",
